      "content": "**Features increasing hERG risk**\n- **Protonatable amine(s):** hERG blockers often present a **cationic center** that can engage in electrostatic interactions within the channel cavity (notably near aromatic residues such as Tyr/Phe).\n- **Aromatic/hydrophobic surface:** the fluorinated aromatic/heteroaromatic region can support **\u03c0/ hydrophobic interactions** within the hERG binding site.",
